ave steam on the one side and need to cool down the steam till you get water again on the other side if you want to get aprox three zero of the energy you or better the uranium brought into the water to let it boil if you only have hot steam on the one and cold steam on the other side you ll loose much more of the energy and so they cool down the steam to get at least the three zero of energy that carnot will give them the cooling towers are for cooling the steam the vapor you ll see is not the steam of the main core circulation because that steam is radioactive the circulation is divided in at least two circuits connected about heat exchangers to prevent radioactive pollution of the environment two nd ok the main core is hot but even in the modernst hightemperature reactors htr they only run at eight zero zero deg celsius this is still verry far away from uraniums melting point which is somewhere around two zero zero zero deg celsius but you ll have lot s of problems with the boiler s steel that s because at this temperature the metal is attacked by steam and will corrode verry fast this is only for bwr s the new he cooled reactors have temperatures up to one two zero zero deg celsius but this is only experimental three rd i personaly think that nuclear waste should be as low as ever possible because the dose you get will accumulate about the years today one mrem and next year zero five mrem won t be zero seven five mrem at all it accumulates and even in eight zero years you ll still have one five mrem and i m not interested in glowing in the night and getting children with two heads this is my point of view only my zero zero two christian reisel student of electronic sciences christian reisel goldammerweg two w six six zero one buebingen germany voice four nine six eight zero five two two one seven nine fax ox p seven r five f zero qy one q sy dz zero l six mmo zero k vhu six mx seven g mf w t nine m q zero four zero end